WEBVTT

00:17.280 --> 00:20.440
Dr.  Leighton, the lifeguard
is on the radio for you.

00:20.560 --> 00:22.000
Put me through.
What do we have here?

00:22.120 --> 00:23.520
The shark shot up like a rocket.

00:23.640 --> 00:25.280
There are three victims,
one of whom is already dead.

00:25.440 --> 00:26.400
These are teenagers, man.

00:26.520 --> 00:28.040
-How far are you?
-Three minutes.

00:28.200 --> 00:30.440
Better hurry up, the whole
beach is covered in blood.

00:30.600 --> 00:31.560
Breaking news.

00:31.680 --> 00:34.360
A shark attack is reported
in Malibu earlier this morning.

00:34.520 --> 00:35.480
You are watching an amateur video...

00:35.600 --> 00:36.560
SHARK ATTACK IN MALIBU

00:36.680 --> 00:38.200
... from the dramatic
scenes on the beach.

00:38.320 --> 00:40.480
One of our reporters
will be on site shortly

00:40.600 --> 00:42.400
and bring you up to
date during the day.

00:47.440 --> 00:48.760
Hello, interns.

00:49.320 --> 00:51.720
I'm Jesse Sallander, the
emergency room chief nurse.

00:52.080 --> 00:55.160
And for the next three
years I'll be your mom.

00:55.800 --> 00:57.880
I can promise you,
nothing is going on

00:58.040 --> 00:59.440
here that your mom
doesn't know about.

01:00.040 --> 01:01.480
You think you are
smarter than your mom

01:01.600 --> 01:03.880
because you are
doctors, but you are not.

01:04.319 --> 01:06.200
Your mama can
tell when you're lying

01:06.400 --> 01:07.640
cries or dies.

01:08.040 --> 01:09.320
Hey, watch out, dude.

01:09.600 --> 01:10.560
It can't stand around here.

01:10.680 --> 01:12.440
Transport couches come in

01:12.560 --> 01:13.520
and out here, every two minutes.

01:14.360 --> 01:15.320
Storage room.

01:15.480 --> 01:16.640
CCCRP?

01:17.040 --> 01:19.240
Combat Casualty Care
Research Program.

01:19.400 --> 01:20.360
Ministry of Defense.

01:20.560 --> 01:22.200
Every year they send us

01:22.320 --> 01:23.440
doctors to show
us new techniques

01:23.560 --> 01:26.040
new technologies
they learned in combat.

01:26.520 --> 01:28.000
That was only a year ago for us.

01:28.120 --> 01:29.080
It feels like a thousand

01:32.120 --> 01:35.440
Every year, thousands
want new doctors like you

01:35.560 --> 01:37.440
Learn emergency
medicine, here in the parish

01:37.560 --> 01:41.080
cathedral, which you
are about to enter.

01:41.680 --> 01:42.960
That is her.

01:43.080 --> 01:44.560
This is Jessamine.

01:44.680 --> 01:45.800
I thought that
was Charlotte Piel.

01:45.920 --> 01:47.920
Jessamine was the
character she played.

01:48.040 --> 01:49.000
Why don't you know something like that?

01:49.160 --> 01:50.120
I don't know any of their films.

01:50.280 --> 01:52.200
You haven't seen
The Artemis Stone?

01:52.360 --> 01:53.960
That was the most influential
movie of my childhood.

01:54.080 --> 01:56.320
The Artemis Fire was the best.
I read the book twice.

01:56.440 --> 01:57.640
The Artemis Thief
was much better.

01:57.800 --> 01:58.920
-You are crazy.
-You're nerds.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.600
Angels Memorial.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.640
Okay, look closely guys.

02:03.960 --> 02:06.400
This is what you will
look like in 12 months.

02:06.520 --> 02:08.400
Tired and insecure.

02:08.520 --> 02:11.480
You sophomores say hello to
those in your sophomore year.

02:12.280 --> 02:14.280
Hi, Miss Piel.
I am Angus Leighton.

02:14.400 --> 02:15.880
I'm a huge fan.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.000
Just call me Charlotte.

02:17.160 --> 02:19.440
No, it's called Dr.  Piel.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.160
I am Malaya Pineda.

02:21.320 --> 02:23.160
-Hi.
-And this is Mario Savetti.

02:23.280 --> 02:24.600
He hasn't seen
any of your films.

02:24.840 --> 02:26.120
It's enough.

02:26.440 --> 02:28.760
Dr.  Leighton, did you come
with your brother today?

02:29.000 --> 02:31.640
-He's got new interns.
-Yes.  I haven't seen him since.

02:31.760 --> 02:32.960
Dr.  Leighton is in the helicopter.

02:33.080 --> 02:34.440
What, is he in the helicopter?

02:34.560 --> 02:36.800
Him and that guy from the Army.
There wasn't enough space because...

02:36.920 --> 02:38.280
Does Dr.  Rorish of it?

02:38.400 --> 02:39.360
What kind of army guy?

02:41.200 --> 02:42.560
Man, I hate helicopters.

02:43.080 --> 02:45.040
It's a miracle that if you
think about it, you even fly.

02:45.200 --> 02:46.160
I do not have it yet...

02:46.560 --> 02:47.520
thought about it.

02:47.640 --> 02:50.280
Yes.  They crash 35%
more often than planes.

02:50.400 --> 02:53.200
9.84 crashes every
100,000 hours.

02:53.960 --> 02:56.720
I did not know that.  Now.

02:58.600 --> 03:01.040
If you're so scared, why
did you hop on board?

03:01.160 --> 03:03.040
I wasn't talking about
fear, I just don't like it.

03:03.760 --> 03:05.400
I don't like bad
tequila either, but

03:05.520 --> 03:06.920
that didn't stop me
yesterday either.

03:08.960 --> 03:10.480
A strong wind is
blowing from the west.

03:10.640 --> 03:12.040
I'll have to land
against the wind.

03:12.240 --> 03:13.680
Well, that's going to be bad now!
Just the rest.

03:19.920 --> 03:22.760
Or?  It's a miracle that it doesn't
fall from the sky like a stone.

03:23.680 --> 03:25.440
Ground contact in eight seconds.

03:26.840 --> 03:29.840
This beach has been closed
by order of the county sheriff.

03:40.600 --> 03:42.560
Take over the girl.
I take the other one.

03:42.680 --> 03:43.640
Understood.

03:47.080 --> 03:48.240
What's your name?

03:48.360 --> 03:49.320
Kaya.

03:49.440 --> 03:52.200
The shark came out of nowhere!
We didn't see him until...

03:52.480 --> 03:53.440
Well what is your name

03:53.560 --> 03:55.000
My name is jaydin.

03:55.120 --> 03:56.840
Jaydin, please calm down now.

03:57.040 --> 03:58.240
OK.

04:00.400 --> 04:01.840
He's losing too much blood.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.440
He won't make it unless
we stabilize him here.

04:07.520 --> 04:08.840
You have to hold still.

04:10.160 --> 04:12.840
She has to get on the stretcher
and then in the helicopter.

04:12.960 --> 04:14.280
-What about Tucker?
-No idea...

04:15.720 --> 04:16.920
Good!  I go!

04:18.360 --> 04:19.800
Stay behind the police line.

04:21.320 --> 04:22.880
Take them away, have
someone take them away.

04:23.320 --> 04:25.200
-What do we have here?
-The guy's goulash.

04:25.360 --> 04:27.640
I need to transfuse
blood while I plug this in.

04:27.880 --> 04:29.200
Connect what?  So what is that?

04:29.320 --> 04:32.080
Bandaging does not work, but
the bleeding must be stopped.

04:32.200 --> 04:34.560
That is why this foam is
injected into the peritoneum.

04:34.680 --> 04:36.400
-Foam?
-He covers everything

04:36.560 --> 04:38.160
the organs, vessels, to everything...

04:38.320 --> 04:39.840
It expands and
tampons the bleeding.

04:39.960 --> 04:41.840
This is called the
intraperitoneal foam system.

04:41.960 --> 04:43.040
With best regards
from the US military.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.920
Are you serious?
Have you done that before?

04:45.720 --> 04:46.680
With a pig.

04:47.280 --> 04:49.200
-A pig?
-It works.

04:50.000 --> 04:50.960
Should work.

04:51.920 --> 04:53.960
Here.  It's like injecting
cream into an eclair.

05:02.440 --> 05:04.960
The blood circulation gets
better, the pulse stronger.

05:05.160 --> 05:07.200
Let's get her out of here.

05:07.600 --> 05:09.240
As you know, the
Army sends one...

05:09.360 --> 05:12.720
To teach, not to send
my teaching doctor out

05:12.840 --> 05:14.440
into the field on the
day his interns start.

05:14.560 --> 05:15.800
This is hardly a home visit.

05:16.040 --> 05:18.400
-You don't have authority...
-I do.

05:21.240 --> 05:22.800
I was told you were
informed on Friday.

05:23.880 --> 05:24.960
What are we talking about now?

05:26.040 --> 05:28.040
The board decided to combine

05:28.200 --> 05:29.960
emergency room
management and trauma 1.

05:30.080 --> 05:31.480
-I beg your pardon?
-Yes.

05:31.600 --> 05:33.120
I am now in charge of both areas.

05:33.240 --> 05:35.040
You can't be serious.

05:35.680 --> 05:37.240
I'm sorry you found out.

05:37.360 --> 05:38.360
I know you are disappointed.

05:38.480 --> 05:40.960
Losing a job that I didn't want?

05:41.160 --> 05:43.040
No, I'm pissed off about the

05:43.200 --> 05:45.080
merger of Trauma
1 with another area

05:45.200 --> 05:47.080
sets the emergency
room back by 40 years.

05:47.200 --> 05:49.120
Just that it's more effective.

05:49.240 --> 05:50.840
More effective for you.

05:51.600 --> 05:52.560
What is happening with me?

05:53.080 --> 05:54.400
You will be a doctor again.

05:55.400 --> 05:56.840
I've always been a doctor.

06:06.880 --> 06:07.840
Grab the door.

06:09.840 --> 06:11.000
Close the door.

06:16.320 --> 06:17.680
Man overboard!

06:17.880 --> 06:19.320
Put on!  We lost a man!

06:24.920 --> 06:26.520
You have to turn around and back.

06:26.640 --> 06:27.880
I have a ramp in the back.

06:28.120 --> 06:29.640
I can't sit up.
Not with the wind!

06:32.200 --> 06:33.440
Fly right over the water.

06:37.480 --> 06:39.360
-What are you doing?
-Something stupid.

06:40.360 --> 06:41.720
Make them an angel!

06:52.920 --> 06:54.200
All right, watch out, guys.

06:54.720 --> 06:56.560
They are doctors.
You are here to learn.

06:56.800 --> 06:59.160
You're out of the
way, you're not a guest.

06:59.640 --> 07:01.800
You are part of the
trauma team, don't be shy.

07:02.000 --> 07:03.840
Well, let's get started,
heads down, careful.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.200
Lady, open the door.

07:11.440 --> 07:13.600
-What do you have here?
-Two shark victims.

07:13.720 --> 07:16.400
A thirteen year
old with multiple

07:16.520 --> 07:18.040
deep wounds on
her right leg and arm.

07:18.160 --> 07:20.040
- A seventeen year old...
- One, two, three.

07:20.160 --> 07:21.640
... with multiple stab
wounds in the abdomen,

07:21.760 --> 07:23.840
he had low blood
pressure, now he's stable.

07:24.040 --> 07:26.600
Well, just a moment.  Pinkney, get
him to the operating room right now.

07:29.040 --> 07:30.360
Moment.
Where are the two doctors?

07:30.480 --> 07:31.440
There was an accident.

07:31.560 --> 07:32.520
Which accident?

07:32.960 --> 07:34.160
Dr.  Leighton fell.

07:34.320 --> 07:35.680
- Fell from where?
- From the helicopter.

07:35.800 --> 07:36.760
From a height of six meters.

07:36.880 --> 07:38.160
-Where are you now?
-No idea.

07:38.520 --> 07:40.160
Army guy Willis is with
him, that's all I know.

07:40.280 --> 07:42.320
Angus, stay here.
Go to the control center.

07:42.480 --> 07:44.040
Find out what
about your brother.

07:46.880 --> 07:48.000
Transport stretcher, watch out.

07:48.160 --> 07:50.560
Michelle, a blood count,
blood group and cross test.

07:50.680 --> 07:51.640
Take over.

07:52.640 --> 07:53.920
Good, get her over here.

07:54.240 --> 07:55.440
Come here.

07:55.600 --> 07:58.080
On three.  One two Three.

07:58.240 --> 07:59.200
I have it.

07:59.360 --> 08:00.320
-What's your name?
-Kaya.

08:00.480 --> 08:02.760
Kaya, all right.  We'll roll you
around once, everything will be fine.

08:02.880 --> 08:04.160
Ready?  One two...

08:04.280 --> 08:05.240
All right.

08:06.440 --> 08:07.680
-Step away.
-All right.

08:07.920 --> 08:08.880
The airways are clear.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.600
Who can tell me the best
place for IV for trauma patients?

08:11.840 --> 08:12.920
Behind you, behind you.

08:13.040 --> 08:14.000
Anybody?

08:14.600 --> 08:16.840
I need a cart with 5-0
vicryl sewing material.

08:17.040 --> 08:18.200
Breathing sounds
evenly on both sides.

08:18.400 --> 08:19.360
Femoral vein?

08:19.480 --> 08:21.600
No.  Hurry, your patient
can't wait for google.

08:21.760 --> 08:23.400
Blood pressure is at 82 over 40.

08:23.720 --> 08:25.240
The belly is soft
and insensitive.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.040
Jesse, Epi with lidocaine, please.

08:27.200 --> 08:28.440
-Right away.
-Thank you.

08:28.880 --> 08:30.080
Tweezers, please.

08:30.760 --> 08:31.840
Tweezers, thank you.

08:32.080 --> 08:33.960
Dr.  Kean, where
is the access going?

08:34.400 --> 08:36.280
Come.  Now please.

08:36.520 --> 08:37.640
-The inner jugular vein?
-No.

08:37.799 --> 08:39.320
The pupils are uniform
and sensitive to light.

08:39.559 --> 08:41.480
The elbow veins allow great

08:41.600 --> 08:42.960
access for immediate
resuscitation.

08:43.480 --> 08:45.600
Well done.  Look here.
Come on and look down.

08:45.760 --> 08:48.600
Here is a 2 cm tear
in the tibial artery.

08:48.760 --> 08:51.360
Come on, Dr.  Piel.
Help me fix it, please.

08:51.480 --> 08:53.080
A sixteen in the
crook of the elbow?

08:53.200 --> 08:54.160
Yes, please.

08:54.280 --> 08:55.240
Jesse.

08:56.120 --> 08:58.960
Mike Leighton fell 6
meters from the helicopter.

09:00.800 --> 09:03.160
Call Dr.  Campbell,
I'm doing a trial

09:03.320 --> 09:04.600
laparotomy, add 2
more units of 0 negative.

09:05.120 --> 09:06.440
Incredible that
this boy is still alive.

09:09.280 --> 09:10.520
What the hell is that stuff?

09:12.000 --> 09:13.720
All right, call Colonel Willis.

09:14.400 --> 09:16.040
It looks like an eclair.

09:19.200 --> 09:20.720
Did you want to
tell me what that

09:20.880 --> 09:21.840
stuff is that oozes
out of the patient?

09:21.960 --> 09:23.520
I've been a bit busy here.

09:23.680 --> 09:24.960
GCS is 6, I'll intubate.

09:25.200 --> 09:26.200
It adapts to the anatomy.

09:26.400 --> 09:27.360
That's what it's about.

09:27.480 --> 09:29.200
I need a 10cc syringe

09:29.400 --> 09:32.320
a 7.5 endotracheal tube,
and is there a CO2 detector?

09:32.960 --> 09:34.680
How am I supposed
to get that out of him?

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
It is designed to
deviate from the organs

09:37.120 --> 09:38.400
without leaving any
surface damage.

09:38.640 --> 09:41.080
You become famous.  It has
never been tried on humans.

09:42.240 --> 09:43.800
Does anyone know where the bleeding is?

09:44.640 --> 09:45.600
Well, we're in.

09:45.720 --> 09:47.200
Probably a mesenteric

09:47.320 --> 09:48.560
root injury, hard to tell.

09:49.400 --> 09:51.520
Is there a status
report on Dr.  Leighton?

09:51.680 --> 09:52.640
Who's there?

09:52.760 --> 09:54.160
Angus, you shouldn't
be on the line.

09:54.320 --> 09:56.520
I go out when I know
how my brother is doing.

09:56.680 --> 09:57.640
Is he conscious?

09:57.800 --> 09:59.360
No, and that doesn't help.

10:00.080 --> 10:01.040
When are you around here?

10:01.160 --> 10:02.120
Angus, get out of there.

10:02.240 --> 10:03.640
Dr.  Leighton, get away
from the microphone.

10:04.680 --> 10:06.440
Boy, let them do their job.

10:07.280 --> 10:09.360
An ambulance
just arrived, help me

10:10.080 --> 10:11.400
or do you need a break?

10:12.960 --> 10:13.920
I'm good.

10:19.880 --> 10:20.840
Okay what's up

10:21.000 --> 10:22.680
Sixty-five year old
Henry Underwood found

10:22.800 --> 10:24.720
unconscious on the
sidewalk after being robbed.

10:25.040 --> 10:26.800
GCS is at 4, he only
responds to pain.

10:26.920 --> 10:28.000
Multiple bruises.

10:28.160 --> 10:31.880
Blood pressure is at 118 to 64,
pulse is at 132, saturation is 87.

10:32.040 --> 10:33.840
Get out of the way, bed number two.

10:33.960 --> 10:36.520
If we take blood from him,
give him 1 liter of saline solution.

10:37.520 --> 10:39.200
On three.  One two Three.

10:41.400 --> 10:42.360
What do you have, Guthrie?

10:42.520 --> 10:45.040
Ambush victim.  Blunt trauma
to the head, back and chest.

10:45.160 --> 10:46.840
-Get the ultrasound machine.
-I?

10:47.600 --> 10:49.040
-Where is it?
-I have it.

10:50.480 --> 10:52.200
You.  What's your name boy

10:52.320 --> 10:53.280
Elliot.

10:53.480 --> 10:54.640
Here you are Dr.  Dixon.

10:54.800 --> 10:56.960
Breathe, Dr.  Dixon.  Breathe.

10:57.680 --> 10:58.640
Interns,

10:59.720 --> 11:00.680
i am dr  Campbell.

11:01.880 --> 11:04.480
Since your teaching
doctor is currently

11:04.600 --> 11:07.160
incapacitated, Dr.
Rorish looks after.

11:07.440 --> 11:08.400
I have to go up to the operating room.

11:08.520 --> 11:10.840
We don't know if he's out of
action.  We don't know anything.

11:11.040 --> 11:12.640
Dr.  Leighton, sorry.
I have not seen her.

11:13.000 --> 11:14.880
Since when has he been
giving instructions to the interns?

11:15.000 --> 11:16.640
-Dr.  Leighton.
-He runs the operating room.

11:16.840 --> 11:19.320
Dr.  Campbell is the new
emergency room manager.

11:20.800 --> 11:23.480
We all hope Mike is fine.

11:26.160 --> 11:27.440
LOS ANGELES FIRE DEPARTMENT

11:33.360 --> 11:34.320
Oh God.

11:34.720 --> 11:36.360
I'm new here.  I am willis.

11:36.600 --> 11:38.040
-Where are we taking him?
-To the Center Stage!

11:40.280 --> 11:41.480
There they come.

11:41.760 --> 11:43.160
-All right.
-Angus, this is Mike.

11:47.320 --> 11:48.880
Was he even conscious?

11:50.520 --> 11:51.760
-Malaya?
-I dont know.

11:52.000 --> 11:53.280
Unfortunately not.

11:53.400 --> 11:55.880
No gag reflex, no reaction.
I had to intubate him.

11:56.040 --> 11:58.160
He has increased intracranial
pressure, he is bleeding.

11:58.520 --> 12:00.360
-I call neurosurgery.
-There is no time for that.

12:00.640 --> 12:01.720
He cramps.

12:03.840 --> 12:04.800
He has a brain prolapse.

12:04.960 --> 12:06.080
I know what cramp means.

12:06.240 --> 12:08.120
Then you know your
brother will die in the

12:08.240 --> 12:09.400
next 60 seconds
without drilling his head.

12:09.520 --> 12:11.120
No, we are waiting
for neurosurgery.

12:11.280 --> 12:13.160
-Risa, the trephine wagon.
-I can use some help.

12:13.320 --> 12:14.360
Malaya, swap with me.

12:15.760 --> 12:17.880
Dr.  Rorish, this is my brother!

12:18.000 --> 12:19.560
Therefore, you shouldn't
make the decision.

12:19.680 --> 12:21.560
-I don't even know him!
-You need to know one thing.

12:21.680 --> 12:23.960
I did about 300 of them
and you probably didn't.

12:24.120 --> 12:26.200
I am the best hope for
your brother.  Now you go.

12:26.640 --> 12:28.000
Angus, let him do
what he has to do.

12:31.320 --> 12:32.960
-You shouldn't see this.
-I can not go.

12:33.480 --> 12:35.760
I'm not forcing you
to go, but stay back.

12:38.880 --> 12:39.840
I drill.

12:59.280 --> 13:00.240
Mike will succeed.

13:00.880 --> 13:02.280
That guy, Colonel Willis...

13:02.640 --> 13:04.320
drills a hole in his skull

13:04.600 --> 13:06.920
on the center stage and
he didn't care what I thought.

13:09.360 --> 13:10.320
It didn't matter to anyone.

13:11.920 --> 13:12.880
Even Rorish.

13:13.360 --> 13:14.960
I know you don't wanna hear this

13:15.520 --> 13:18.320
but to me it looked like
he had saved his life.

13:23.400 --> 13:25.720
I have no news
except that he is alive.

13:26.920 --> 13:28.480
OK.  When does he wake up?

13:28.920 --> 13:31.040
We'll leave it sedated
and open for at least

13:31.160 --> 13:32.120
a few days until the
swelling goes away.

13:32.240 --> 13:33.840
We should have brought
him up here immediately.

13:33.960 --> 13:36.120
Mike would be dead if it
wasn't for Willis.  It is a fact.

13:36.600 --> 13:37.560
I already said that.

13:46.680 --> 13:47.640
Where's tucker

13:47.920 --> 13:48.880
He's in the operating room.

13:50.280 --> 13:52.560
His parents are on the
plane, we couldn't reach them.

